[
    {
        "text": "\"Spring forward, fall back,\" as the saying goes.",
        "startTime": 185,
        "endTime": 2836,
        "slowStartTime": 427,
        "slowEndTime": 4479
    },
    {
        "text": "Many countries change their clocks twice a year to observe Daylight Saving Time.",
        "startTime": 3011,
        "endTime": 6616,
        "slowStartTime": 4666,
        "slowEndTime": 10149
    },
    {
        "text": "The practice was first introduced in Europe during the first World War...",
        "startTime": 7137,
        "endTime": 10135,
        "slowStartTime": 10855,
        "slowEndTime": 15427
    },
    {
        "text": "...but was only fully adopted towards the end of the 20th century.",
        "startTime": 10259,
        "endTime": 13251,
        "slowStartTime": 15538,
        "slowEndTime": 20101
    },
    {
        "text": "The idea was to take advantage of the longer summer days by gaining an extra hour of daylight...",
        "startTime": 15080,
        "endTime": 19726,
        "slowStartTime": 22770,
        "slowEndTime": 29814
    },
    {
        "text": "...and shortening the days in winter",
        "startTime": 19888,
        "endTime": 21419,
        "slowStartTime": 29982,
        "slowEndTime": 32354
    },
    {
        "text": "It wasn't a new concept.",
        "startTime": 23135,
        "endTime": 24474,
        "slowStartTime": 34852,
        "slowEndTime": 36936
    },
    {
        "text": "Back in 1784, American inventor and politician Benjamin Franklin...",
        "startTime": 24775,
        "endTime": 28460,
        "slowStartTime": 37313,
        "slowEndTime": 42915
    },
    {
        "text": "...suggested that starting the day earlier in the summer...",
        "startTime": 28535,
        "endTime": 30705,
        "slowStartTime": 42953,
        "slowEndTime": 46283
    },
    {
        "text": "...would save a considerable number of candles.",
        "startTime": 30787,
        "endTime": 33091,
        "slowStartTime": 46330,
        "slowEndTime": 49861
    },
    {
        "text": "Those in favor of the practice saying today's energy-consuming society...",
        "startTime": 35268,
        "endTime": 38718,
        "slowStartTime": 53052,
        "slowEndTime": 58302
    },
    {
        "text": "...the environmental benefits linked to changing the clocks are considerable.",
        "startTime": 38809,
        "endTime": 42077,
        "slowStartTime": 58364,
        "slowEndTime": 63341
    },
    {
        "text": "While only small amounts of electricity are saved per household, added up they can be significant.",
        "startTime": 42295,
        "endTime": 46969,
        "slowStartTime": 63593,
        "slowEndTime": 70679
    },
    {
        "text": "Lobby groups however argue these savings are negligible, particularly in the winter...",
        "startTime": 49143,
        "endTime": 53043,
        "slowStartTime": 73864,
        "slowEndTime": 79789
    },
    {
        "text": "...when the afternoon advantage is offset by the need for more light in the darker mornings.",
        "startTime": 53121,
        "endTime": 57286,
        "slowStartTime": 79832,
        "slowEndTime": 86154
    },
    {
        "text": "Farmers cite other disadvantages, for example the unsettling effect on cows...",
        "startTime": 57611,
        "endTime": 61593,
        "slowStartTime": 86566,
        "slowEndTime": 92614
    },
    {
        "text": "...as milking cycles are disrupted.",
        "startTime": 61689,
        "endTime": 63233,
        "slowStartTime": 92684,
        "slowEndTime": 95074
    },
    {
        "text": "The elderly, the sick and children are also thought to have difficulties adapting.",
        "startTime": 63515,
        "endTime": 67117,
        "slowStartTime": 95423,
        "slowEndTime": 100900
    }
]